wikipedia_page.main: Joseph George O'Gorman (24 July 1890 – 26 August 1974)  was a British entertainer and cricketer. With his brother Dave (1894–1964) he formed a song, dance and comedy act called the O'Gorman Brothers. Starting by touring the variety halls of England, in the 1930s they also became popular in the United States and earned a fortune.
